.H 2 "DCE Administration Utilities"
.P
.iX "-[" "administering DCE" "utilities"
The following subsections describe the utility programs that DCE provides for
managing and maintaining the DCE software.  The last subsection tells
you which utilities to place on a machine that is
specially configured for the remote administration of DCE servers.
.H 3 "DCE Control Program"
.P
.iX "\*Ldcecp\*O"
The overall administration tool for DCE, \*Ldcecp\*O, has
functions for administering the DCE services.  You cannot use the program to
administer GDS and DFS.
.P
The \*Ldcecp\*O utility is included in all of the DCE server software
packages, except GDS and DFS.
.H 3 "Security Service Administration Programs"
.iX "-[" "Security Service" "administration utilities"
.P
The Security Service provides the following administration utilities:
.ML
.LI
The \*Lsec_create_db\*O utility creates the Security database and sets up
some configuration files.
.LI
The \*Lsec_salvage_db\*O command helps you recover from possible program
errors and data corruption.  The \*Lsec_salvage_db\*O command applies internal
consistency checks to the Security database (registry)
and fixes internal data structure problems.
You can also use \*Lsec_salvage_db\*O to generate an ASCII version of the
registry that can be edited and reconstructed, if necessary.
.LI
The \*Lpasswd_import\*O command allows you create registry entries based on the group and password files from machines that do not implement DCE Security.
.LI
The \*Lpasswd_export\*O command allows you to update the UNIX \*L/etc/passwd\*O and \*L/etc/group\*O files with current user information obtained from the registry.
.LI
The \*Lpasswd_override\*O file allows you to establish overrides to the information contained in the registry.
.LE
.iX "-]" "Security Service" "administration utilities"
.H 3 "CDS Administration Programs"
.iX "Cell Directory Service (CDS)" "administration utilities"
.P
CDS provides the CDS Browser (\*Lcdsbrowser\*O) utility, which
is a Motif-based program useful for viewing
the contents and structure of the CDS namespace.
.H 3 "GDS Administration Programs"
.iX "Global Directory Service (GDS)" "administration utility"
.P
The \*Lgdsditadm\*O program supports administration of the contents of the
local DUA cache database and the GDS database, both local and remote.
.H 3 "DFS Administration Programs"
.iX "Distributed File Service (DFS)" "administration utilities"
.P
DFS provides the following administration utilities:
.ML
.LI
The \*Lsalvage\*O process checks the DCE LFS file system for internal
consistency and corrects errors it finds.
.LI
The \*Lfts\*O commands help you manage filesets.
.LI
The \*Lbak\*O commands help you perform backup tasks.
.LI
The \*Lcm\*O commands help you customize the performance of the Cache Manager and examine features of DFS.
.LI
The \*Lbos\*O commands help you contact the Basic OverSeer
(BOS) server used to monitor processes on server machines in your cell.
You can also use the \*Lbos\*O commands to perform some Security tasks.
.LI
The \*Lscout\*O program helps you monitor the File Exporters
running on File Server machines.
You may want to install \*Lscout\*O only on the system administrator's 
DFS client machine.
.LI
The \*Lnewaggr\*O command can format a raw disk partition for use as a DCE LFS
aggregate.
.LI
The \*Ldfsexport\*O command makes DCE LFS aggregates and non-LFS partitions
available to remote users through use of the File Exporter.
.LE
.iX "-]" "administering DCE" "utilities"
.H 3 "Programs for DCE Remote Administration Machines"
.P
You may decide to configure a machine for the remote administration of
the DCE servers.  The administration utilities that need to be installed,
in addition to the DCE client software, are the following:
.ML
.LI
The \*Lpasswd_override\*O, \*Lsec_admin\*O, \*Lsec_create_db\*O, 
and \*Lsec_salvage_db\*O programs must be installed for Security
service administration.
.LI
The \*Lgdsditadm\*O and \*Lgdscp\*O for GDS administration.
.LI
The \*Lbak\*O, \*Lbos\*O, \*Lcm\*O, \*Ldfsexport\*O, \*Lfts\*O, \*Lnewaggr\*O,
\*Lsalvage\*O, \*Lscout\*O programs for DFS administration. 
.LE
.P
No software other than \*Ldcecp\*O and the DCE client software
is needed for administering DCE RPC, DTS, Security, or CDS.
.H 2 "Application Development Environment Machine"
.iX "application development machines"
.P
A DCE machine can also be configured for
the development of DCE applications.
This involves adding to the basic DCE client configuration several
include (\*L.h\*O) and interface specification (\*L.idl\*O) files,
along with the \*Lidl\*O program.





